<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Malai Rice Recipe</title>
	<link href="~/css/malairice.css" rel="stylesheet" />
</head>
<body>

    <header>
        <h1>Malai Rice Recipe</h1>
    </header>

    <section class="recipe-container">

        <div class="ingredients">
            <h2>Ingredients</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>2 cups Basmati Rice</li>
                <li>1 cup Fresh Cream (Malai)</li>
                <li>2 tbsp Butter</li>
                <li>1 tsp Cumin Seeds</li>
                <li>2 Green Chilies (chopped)</li>
                <li>1 Onion (finely chopped)</li>
                <li>1/2 cup Milk</li>
                <li>Salt to taste</li>
                <li>Fresh Coriander for garnish</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="instructions">
            <h2>Instructions</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>Wash and soak the Basmati rice for 20 minutes, then drain.</li>
                <li>In a pan, heat butter and add cumin seeds.</li>
                <li>Add chopped onions and green chilies, sauté until golden brown.</li>
                <li>Add the soaked rice and stir for a minute.</li>
                <li>Pour in milk and fresh cream, then mix well.</li>
                <li>Add salt and cook on low heat until rice is fully cooked.</li>
                <li>Garnish with fresh coriander and serve hot.</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </section>

</body>
</html>
